main event: A housewife in Cambria, Wisconsin spotted an unidentified oblong object in the sky on March 2, 1966.
interesting points: The object was slightly larger than an automobile, blinking red and green in color, and had propeller-like appendages.
The object moved from northwest to southeast, then turned south and then north, passing in front of the observer's automobile.
The sighting lasted for 5 minutes, and the object disappeared from view when the observer turned to watch the road.
The weather conditions were clear with good visibility, and there was no unusual activity or air traffic in the area.
